         "id": "63cd6dbe-463f-40af-ae48-3ab7d6065286",
         "title": "Ângelo Freire:‌ “Anyone can learn an instrument. But not everyone can play the soul or the language attached to that instrument“",
         "description": "<p><span>Angelo Freire has spent most of his life slightly out of view, shaping the sound of contemporary fado from the place where it is built rather than displayed. A prodigy of the Portuguese guitar, he has accompanied some of the most decisive voices of the genre and, in doing so, helped carry a tradition that is both rigorously codified and quietly alive. Listen to him and his Portuguese guitar on the podcast “The Heart & Hustle of Portugal”</span></p>",
